args:
Deep within the mine, the party locates a
magical weapon from an ancient civilization.
With the prince having found her secret, Chelle
presents him with a choice: obey or die.
Unwilling to watch her people suffer, the prince
takes a third option and attacks the weapon.
One'a these guys again, huh?\nLooks kinda different than the\nlast one, though...
Stop, Luca! Don't just bumble toward it!
Could this really be one of the ancient\nmagical weapons of legend...?
You know of this weapon, Leif?

In the great war of antiquity, armies fought
with mindless soldiers and soulless fiends.
The tales claimed they were all destroyed
or otherwise lost, and yet...
I thought this was just a materium mine.\nWhat is this thing even DOING here?
These are ruins from ancient times—\nhence why they yield materium.
It seems our princess found more than\nmere precious stones here.
Yes, if I had to guess, I'd say she likely\nexcavated this weapon as well.
And then kept it all for herself, eh?\nSuppose I can't blame her, what with\ntimes bein' what they are.
I don't like the vibes this thing gives off.\nI don't like them one BIT.
That's because it is a device from the\nancient Dyrenell Empire. Such things\nare not pleasant for dragons.
How could Chelle stoop to using\nsomething so vile?
Explain yourself, Chelle!\nWhat is this thing doing here?!
Well, I suppose there's no point\nin dissembling now.
This is the Gran Criminale—a weapon of\nalmost unspeakable power, and one I will\nuse to seize control of the continent.
I will use it to rip apart any who aid and\nabet the Empire! I will raze the very dirt\non which they stand to cinder and ash!
Surely there is no need for such cruelty!
Most of the Empire's people obey their\nleaders out of fear for their own lives!\nWould you see them punished as well?!

Those of low birth should think only of
devoting themselves to MY just rule.
The continued existence of any who
refuse to bend the knee holds no value.
You talked a big game, but THIS thing was\nin your back pocket the whole time!
Guess we know who you really are now.
A lady must wear many faces in this world.
You fed us honeyed words while this thing\nlurked beneath our feet? How vile you are!
As a general rule, people who venture\nthis deep into my mine don't live to\nspread the tale around.
And yet, given that you ARE my brother,\nI suppose I could let it slide just this once.
...If you fall in line, that is.
Meaning you want me to obey you\nand fight the Empire on YOUR terms.
Exactly! If you help me take the throne,\nI will permit your continued existence.
Enough talk—the time for decisions is\nupon us. Shall we be bosom companions\nonce more, as in our childhood?

I'm sorry, Chelle, but I can't do that.
I can't follow you so long as you intend
to do such harm to innocent people
all across this land.
He's right! Hell, if you go around attackin'\neverybody who won't swear to serve you,\nyou're no different than the Empire!

Be careful to name me villain so quickly,
sylvan—for only a fool would seek to
govern on the strength of their hopes
and good ideals alone.
But what wisdom is there in believing\na rule without hopes or ideals could\ntruly bring happiness to people?

I dream of a kingdom where everyone
can pursue happiness and peace—and
if I have to put your dream down to see
that happen, that's what I will do!
A shame your skull is far thicker than\nit appears, my dear brother.
Very well.\nIf you will not fall in line...
Then you will be the first to become ash!
Take command of the fiends in these ruins\nand grind these intruders into dust!
Farewell, Brother. And you as well, Leif.\nParting is such sorrow, but I fear this is\nthe destiny of any who vie for dominance.
Get back here and face us, ya coward!\n...Well, hell. If them fiends all decide to\nrush us, we're gonna be in a world'a hurt.
We can't allow my sister's plan to come\nto fruition, no matter what.
We're going to take out this thing and\nshow her the power of our solidarity!
